11. Patents.

A "contributor" is a copyright holder who authorizes the conveyance of
its work.  Contributors grant a non-exclusive, worldwide, royalty-free
patent license to make, use, sell, offer for sale, import and otherwise
run, modify and propagate the contents of its contributor version.

If you convey a covered work, you also have to ensure that the
conveyance is made under patent licenses adequate to give the recipient
the rights to run, modify and propagate the work for the terms of this
License.  If you convey a covered work in object code form, the patent
